cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a novel hybrid-duplex scheme for heterogeneous networks and analyzes the signal-to-interference-plus-noise-ratio and spectral efficiency for both downlink and uplink channels. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper analyzes the spectral efficiency of the proposed scheme and formulates a sum rate maximization problem. 
3. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) - The paper proposes a scheme for improving the performance of heterogeneous networks and analyzes the signal-to-interference-plus-noise-ratio and spectral efficiency. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a scheme for switching the duplex mode of each user based on received power and formulates a sum rate maximization problem. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The proposed scheme can potentially improve the performance of multimedia applications in heterogeneous networks, which may require high data rates and low latency.
